{{Anglican Portal}}''' David Edward Bentley''' (born [[7 August]] [[1935]]) is a former [[Bishop of Lynn]] and [[Bishop of Gloucester|Gloucester]]. Educated at the [[University of Leeds]] and [[Westcott House, Cambridge]], he was ordained in 1961<ref> Debrett's People of Today: (1992, London,[[Debrett's]]) ISBN 1870520092</ref> and began his ministry with [[Curate|curacies]] at ''St Ambrose [[Whitehall, Bristol|Bristol]]'' and ''Holy Trinity with St Mary, [[Guildford]]''<ref>[http://www.holytrinityguildford.org.uk/Index-frameset.htm Church web site]</ref>; after which he was [[Rector]] of [[Headley, East Hampshire]]<ref>[[Crockford's clerical directory]]1975-76 Lambeth, Church House ISBN 0108153674</ref>, [[Rural Dean]] of [[Esher]] and (his final position before elevation to the [[episcopate]]) [[Warden]] of the  ''Community of All Hallows, [[Ditchingham]]'' <ref>[[Who's Who]] 1992 London, [[A & C Black]], 1991 ISBN 0713635142</ref>. 
